This article is a memorandum from former President Barack Obama regarding the unexpected urgent refugee and migration needs related to the Horn of Africa. The memorandum states that the President determines it is important to the national interest to provide assistance under the Migration and Refugee Assistance Act of 1962. This assistance will be in the form of $10 million from the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund, and it will be used to meet the urgent needs of refugees and migrants, including contributions to various organizations and payment of administrative expenses. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.